00:04:40.390 --> 00:04:44.090
What we then barreled into were
the three major building blocks

00:04:44.090 --> 00:04:46.460
for thinking about the
evolution of behavior

00:04:46.460 --> 00:04:49.140
in the framework of contemporary
evolutionary thinking.

00:04:49.140 --> 00:04:52.040
Number one,
individual selection--

00:04:52.040 --> 00:04:54.310
passing on as many
copies of your own genes

00:04:54.310 --> 00:04:56.460
to the next
generation as possible

00:04:56.460 --> 00:04:59.430
by way of your own reproducing.

00:04:59.430 --> 00:05:01.460
The individual
selection-- a chicken

00:05:01.460 --> 00:05:03.130
is an egg's way to
make another egg.

00:05:03.130 --> 00:05:05.510
I've now rehearsed that, so
I've got that down right.

00:05:05.510 --> 00:05:09.290
The whole notion of behavior as
just being this epi-phenomenon

00:05:09.290 --> 00:05:12.780
in order to do what's needed to
get another copy of the genes

00:05:12.780 --> 00:05:14.450
into the next generation.

00:05:14.450 --> 00:05:16.770
Building block number two.

00:05:16.770 --> 00:05:19.840
Some of the time, the best way
to increase the number of genes

00:05:19.840 --> 00:05:21.610
you pass on to the
next generation

00:05:21.610 --> 00:05:25.330
is to help your relatives
do so following that logic

00:05:25.330 --> 00:05:27.560
of Mendelian relatedness.

00:05:27.560 --> 00:05:29.720
And people in the
catch-up section, I know,

00:05:29.720 --> 00:05:33.650
went over issues of, why is it
that you share half your genes

00:05:33.650 --> 00:05:36.770
with a full sibling, a quarter
with a half sibling, et cetera?

00:05:36.770 --> 00:05:41.100
So sometimes the way to maximize
is by helping out a relative

00:05:41.100 --> 00:05:43.570
to do so with,
again, constrained

00:05:43.570 --> 00:05:46.360
by this vicious
mathematical logic of,

00:05:46.360 --> 00:05:49.340
it depends on how related
you are to the relative.

00:05:49.340 --> 00:05:51.910
And thus, you will
gladly lay down your life

00:05:51.910 --> 00:05:55.540
for one identical twin, two
full siblings, eight cousins.

00:05:55.540 --> 00:05:56.920
Off you go.

00:05:56.920 --> 00:06:00.360
So the whole notion
there of insight into why

00:06:00.360 --> 00:06:03.980
social animals the galaxy
over are so obsessed

00:06:03.980 --> 00:06:06.930
with kinship and
relatedness, the whole world

00:06:06.930 --> 00:06:10.320
of who counts as an us,
who counts as a them

00:06:10.320 --> 00:06:12.260
in terms of
cooperative behaviors

00:06:12.260 --> 00:06:14.970
playing out along
lines of relatedness.

00:06:14.970 --> 00:06:19.310
Finally, we saw the third piece,
which was reciprocal altruism.

00:06:19.310 --> 00:06:21.590
You scratch my back,
I'll scratch yours.

00:06:21.590 --> 00:06:25.140
Many hands make the task
less scratchy or whatever.

00:06:25.140 --> 00:06:27.170
And what you see in
those cases, there

00:06:27.170 --> 00:06:30.330
is a whole world
in which you don't

00:06:30.330 --> 00:06:32.640
have to be related
to have cooperation.

00:06:32.640 --> 00:06:35.120
And we saw all the
domains of that bringing

00:06:35.120 --> 00:06:38.150
in the formalization--
biomechanics person

00:06:38.150 --> 00:06:41.270
figuring out how strong
a leg bone has to be.

00:06:41.270 --> 00:06:43.900
A game theorist figuring
out within the realm

00:06:43.900 --> 00:06:46.240
of social behavior
when you cooperate

00:06:46.240 --> 00:06:48.990
and when you don't and
what sort of strategies.

00:06:48.990 --> 00:06:51.240
Game theory, of seeing
the prisoner's dilemma

00:06:51.240 --> 00:06:54.530
as the building block
of that entire field

00:06:54.530 --> 00:06:58.640
and seeing all the strategies
worked out by mathematicians

00:06:58.640 --> 00:07:02.050
and economists and diplomats
and seeing which ones optimize

00:07:02.050 --> 00:07:03.470
under what circumstance.

00:07:03.470 --> 00:07:05.340
And then going and
look in the real world

00:07:05.340 --> 00:07:08.510
and seeing there's all
sorts of animals out there

00:07:08.510 --> 00:07:12.670
that have evolved optimization
strategies of when to cooperate

00:07:12.670 --> 00:07:13.990
and when to defect.

00:07:13.990 --> 00:07:17.580
And what we'll get to as a huge,
huge issue by the time we get

